Here you can see how we spent our summer last year. 😄 (to be honest this summer is not that different, but we're now sitting in an office instead of our basement😂). On May 12th 2020, we appeared on the biggest startup TV show in Austria. At that time, we didn't have a single ready assembled REELOQ in stock, because our producer had to shut down the factory for 2 months due to corona. That's why we only had all the individual parts of our REELOQ. We thought that there would be a maximum of 50 mountaineers among the viewers of the TV show and we watched our broadcast almost relaxed (or as relaxed you can be when you see your face on TV!! 😱). Only a few hours later, we were completely sold out and didn't know how we should cope with the incredible amount of orders. With every new order that came in, we got even more nervous. But still: we had to get to work and assemble our beloved REELOQs. 🔨 For weeks we sat in our basement and, with the help of the best friends and family we could think of, assembled more than a thousand REELOQs ourselves until our manufacturer was able to deliver again. 😅 Those were really exhausting weeks that we definitely didn't expect, but in retrospect it's a funny memory and an important part of our big adventure. We are already excited about the unexpected twists and turns that are yet to come! Stay tuned. 💥 👏

Those who have seen our Q&A about our first business year already know: behind REELOQ there is not only a long company story, but also a really cheesy love story. 😅 We met in November 2018 and clicked great right away. Over the past few years we have noticed HOW GOOD we work together, no matter how many downs and stressful times there were, we never lost our humour. After 2.5 years we can also proudly say that we have never (!) got on each other's nerves or argued. What certainly helps us is that neither of us has to assert his ego and we value each other too much to think we know it better than the other one. We are both eternally grateful for the unbelieveable luck of finding each other, looking forward to work every day and working towards our shared vision with full passion. And for the past year, not only as business partners, but also as a couple ♥️ 😍😍😍 super Team 😍🔥👏 Mei schee 🤗✨ Ihr zwei Süßen 😍 ❤️ so goldig 😮😳👍😎😍😍😍😍❤️ Ihr seits einfach unglaublich süß 😍 und eure Geschichte ist toll! Und ich bewundern echt euren Mut 👏👏👏 super! weiter so 👏😍 ❤️😍 ❤️❤️ Maaaa mega lieb 😍😍😍😍😍 Power couple ❤️ 😍❤️

We have been looking forward to the release of this interview for a long time! 😍 Julia had the honor to interview Christian Stangl, who holds a total of 3 Guinness world records. He has climbed the highest peaks of all continents for 7 years and holds records in "Skyrunning". 😱 In our interview he tells us - how he had the idea to start the project - which challenges he had to overcome - why he had to became a scientist and butterfly collector 😂 - what it's like to be on the road alone for 34 days without any social connection - and why he rode his bike for 38 days to the last summit in the Caucasus. 🚴🏼 Christian for sure has some incredible stories to tell. If you want to feel a really big portion of adventure - make sure to read it!                               Chris Stangl den höchsten Respekt!!!
